The paper deals with a computer vision task, specifically semantic image segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian processes (GP) for learning and identifying reliable annotations, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep features, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the method, which is a common concern in information retrieval (cs.IR) and large-scale data analysis.
